The paper proposes a deep learning method for Extreme Multi-label classification, which is a subfield of machine learning. The method involves a word-vector-based self-attention and a ranking-based AutoEncoder architecture. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also mentions the use of efficient attention mechanisms and feature representation, which could fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
